cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper proposes a deep learning architecture for generating 3D mesh models from single RGB images, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) research. The use of a graph-based convolutional neural network and the adoption of a coarse-to-fine strategy suggest that the paper may also fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Finally, the paper involves experiments with 3D shape estimation, which may also place it under multimedia (cs.MM) category.
